{"author":"RebarBotNava","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"alias":"effusive-sportive-sapsucker","creation_channel":"cli","description":"## Symptom\nAfter a ticket advances from the planning to the execution plan-review phase (via\n`claim`, which sets `plan_review_phase=execution`), running `rebar review-plan <id>`\n— even with `--force` — refreshes the ORIGINAL planning-phase attestation instead of\nminting a fresh execution-phase one. The plan-review CLOSE gate then rejects the close\nwith `incompatible-phase: planning -> execution (incompatible)`, and there is no\nnon-escape-hatch way to produce the execution attestation the close requires.\n\n## Root cause\n`src/rebar/llm/plan_review/__init__.py`: the idempotence short-circuit is guarded by\n`if sign and not force:` (line ~581), but the progressive drift-refresh immediately\nbelow is guarded only by `if sign:` (line ~590) — it omits `and not force`. The\ndocstring/comment at line ~580 explicitly states \"`force` bypasses BOTH this skip and\nthe drift-refresh, forcing a full re-review\", so the code contradicts its own\ndocumented contract. `orchestrator.drift_refresh` re-signs `cand[\"manifest\"]` (the\nprior planning manifest) via `attest.refresh_attestation`, preserving `review-phase:\nplanning`; it never reconsiders phase against the ticket's now-`execution` state.\n\n## Trigger conditions\nThe prior (planning) attestation is stale ONLY by code drift (ticket material +\ncriteria registry unchanged) — e.g. the planning review was signed at one sha and the\nimplementation later landed at another — so `drift_refresh_candidate` matches and the\nprobe passes. Observed live landing ticket f5c0-46ce-fab1-487a: planning review signed\nat sha b5585d65 (main checkout), code merged at f48a2fb41; post-claim `review-plan\n--force` returned `coverage.drift_refresh=true` with a planning manifest, and\n`transition in_progress closed` failed `incompatible-phase`.\n\n## Proposed fix\nChange the drift-refresh guard to `if sign and not force:` so `--force` performs a full\nre-review (honoring the documented contract and minting an execution-phase attestation).\nAlternatively/additionally, `drift_refresh` should decline (return None) when the\nticket's current phase has advanced past the candidate manifest's phase, so an\nexecution-phase ticket never refreshes a planning-phase attestation.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] On an `in_progress` ticket whose only-valid attestation is planning-phase and\n      whose reviewed code has drifted, `rebar review-plan <id> --force` runs a full\n      review (no drift-refresh) and signs an execution-phase attestation.\n- [ ] After that, `transition <id> in_progress closed` passes the plan-review close\n      gate (no `incompatible-phase`).\n- [ ] A regression test covers the planning-attestation + code-drift + phase-advance\n      close path (extends tests/interfaces/lifecycle/test_plan_policy_dogfood.py).\n- [ ] The line ~580 comment and the code guard agree.\n\n## File impact\n- src/rebar/llm/plan_review/__init__.py (drift-refresh force guard)\n- src/rebar/llm/plan_review/orchestrator.py (optional: phase-advance decline)\n- tests/interfaces/lifecycle/test_plan_policy_dogfood.py (regression)","id":"1d9b-56a1-23e0-43c2","parent_id":"","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"bug","title":"plan-review --force does not bypass drift-refresh; execution-phase attestation cannot be minted after planning review + code drift, blocking close"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784847216226822001,"uuid":"67b3024e-d90d-4b8c-a76c-fcfb47811d51"}